snippet.textDisplay: Am actually thinking now that Man City are favorites as they're the only english club to win the first leg but let's see the next legs. Barca are okay but have work to do; injuries aren't helping them. Atletico can do good if they do what simeone wants and let the new players adjust to his system. Very surprised with how good Atalanta are playing, underdogs for this competition. Enjoying Dortmund's style of play so far but PSG could go through if they play as a team and not rely on Mbappe and Neymar all the time. Lyon played well tactically and are playing as a team should. Juventus seem lacking in finishing and seem dazed. Napoli played well against barcelona and also admire the formation they used, also mildly surprised on how the sacking of Ancelotti hasn't affected them poorly, but Gattuso is doing well (still feel bad to how Ancelotti was sacked). Bayern also seem to be clicking but Chelsea were never clinical with their chances, and the thing they're missing is pace. They could've scored if they had fast players, but it's also the lack of preparation for the youngsters on their team. Liverpool dont have issues either but seems like their attacking trio need to communicate and command the ball more, not just focus on Salah. It just seems like Firmino is tasked with assisting to Salah and Mane is there to dribble past opponents but that can only get you so far, other than that, Liverpool still playing good and with the same attacking mindset of the left and right backs. You have to be fully focused to play in this competition  and not make mistakes, as it'll hurt you. Playing in the champions league, you must show your qualities and why you want to play for this prestigious tournament and to win the final. Focus on that and have the mentality.
